This is a 6 part Minigame map I developed a long time ago for CSGO, however due to issues it never worked and was thoroughly broken.

Since I was bugged enough about the old one, I figured it was about time I got around to this.

Enjoy!

**C4**
T's are forced into shelter inside a small yet simple house to guard the planted C4, while CT's must battle their way through and defuse the bomb.

**RUN**
Teams must contend with each other by having at least one member of either team reach the end of the obstacle course.

**GRA**
M3's with low gravity, set with simple high reaching platforms.

**HP+**
Teams battle each other with knifes and augs.
Each player starts with 1000hp.

**AWP**
Teams battle it out with awps over a long distance with simple cover.

**H20**
The grid is instantly enveloped with water, while all players are equipped with knifes to battle it out.

A horribly twisted map of no logical sense whatsoever. Upside-down rooms, black voids, impossible staircases, and creepy noises everywhere to enhance the atmosphere.

Killing each other is no big challenge, since the spawn points of the two teams are closely together and easily accessable. Yet, the great amount of small tunnels connecting the major rooms are enough to confuse you.

Remember that one map? That one that was said to be grand, but was less than that, due to some stupidish bugs and a crash here and there? Remember that one? This map is a little like that one, but more grand, more amazing, and hopefully less crashy. 

-= **Overview** =-

Based on the build puzzle series on hl2dm, this map focuses on teamwork, uniqueness (not anymore as some ideas have already been used in other maps), and fun. No more will you have to pass that damned bunnyhop level, just to get to your favorite jumping level. The map has 20 levels, all connected by a lobby. Go into a teleporter, spawn at a level, finish it, get some points, then pick another one. Finished levels light up green. However, you can still go play that level if you want to! It's a fun map with around 24 people, as if there is more then it tends to get a bit crowded. 

-= **Levels** =-

1) Art of Rotation - Jump over on that moving thing, onto the next, nothing really new here.

2) Rafting - Rambo the rafts across the magical floating river. Sure you can float over there, but you still need a raft to make the jump.

3) Explosive Golf - Little ball things, holes, and grenades. Took me a while to figure out too.

4) Lost in the Clouds - Colored holes correspond to the platforms. Toss a grenade to move one to have a teammate travel across.

5) Find the Nothing - Shoot around below you to find the path. Particles mean you can walk on it.

6) Stuck in Traffic - Dodge the cars until you get to the end. Double cars are your real threat here.
 
7) Up Yours Gravity - Some really easy low gravity jumping. Nothing special here.

8) Light 'Em Up - Use your flashlight to find the way to the end.

9) The Domino Effect - Hit E on the keyboard to spawn the blocks. Afterwards, just hop across. If they fall, hit E on the keyboard to respawn them again.

10) Man The Cannons - Shoot your teammates onto platforms where buttons are. All buttons break the gate underneath you. 

11) Rolling Stones - Push a ball across a chasm. You can walk on the air, the ball can't.

12) Wet n Wild - Waterclimb all the way to the end.

13) Spin me right round - Get to the end.

14) Trial and Error - Find your way to the end. SPRAYS HELP HERE.

15) Dumb Luck - Totally random. Sometimes it can be a total bitch.

16) Smoking Kills - Toss them smokes over the wall and onto the CT's heads.

17) Wishing Well Doesn't Work Against Death - The only dieing level, knife your way to the end. Try not to drown.

18) Doin' Something Stupid - Jump on a plane. Simple.

19) Could not think of a name for this - Use the spinny thing to get to the end.

20) Lasers - Don't get hit on your way to the end of the hallway. 


-= **Changes (That I can remember**) =-

-Removed island

-Added secrets

-Changed level 9

-Changed lobby

-Added lobby poster

-Decorated

-Fixed some bugs

-Changed level 13


-= **Known Bugs** =-

-Sometimes the map will end early. This happens when 2 people finish a level at the same time, so it adds "2" instead of "1" to the final counter, which triggers the ending. Nothing I can do about this, but it should be a fairly rare bug.

-= **Notes** =-

So, this pain is back. There's been a lot of changes that I made over the course of month long intermissions of working on it, so I can't really list them all out.

You can use any part of this map, as I left it unprotected against decompiling. Steal ideas? Whatever, just please the least you can do is CREDIT ME.

Umm, you might've seen some previous versions around, but rest assured, that MG_GRAND_PUZZLES_F IS THE LATEST VERSION (AS OF RIGHT NOW).

Erm, go Steam Gamers? I don't really remember adding their banner, but it's a great community nonetheless. That wasn't advertizing, it was praising. 

Have fun! 

Might be the first of a series, dunno yet.

mg_grand_puzzles Map By: DisConNecTed THIS MAP REQUIRES FAST DOWNLOAD, IF YOU DON'T HAVE A FAST DOWNLOAD SET UP, NAVIGATE YOUR FACE AWAY FROM THE PRESENCE OF THIS WEB PAGE
Lately, I've been really upset with the quality of some MG maps that have been coming out, especially the obstacle ones. No offense or anything...its just that, well, its not that hard to add lighting or use different textures. And I think it gets boring to everyone to just jump from one platform to another, or dodge a laser. So, I'm hoping that people will see this map, look around the site, read some tutorials, and release some rocking maps. This map is a 6 month pain in the... Well, this version is only a few weeks. See, this started out as bob4, looked EXACTLY like the original one: no lighting, details, nada. So, I went to play some hl2dm coop, and came across these js_build_puzzle maps by D@sole. I only played 3: fourteen, 11, and whatever the space one was, but I had a pretty good idea how they functioned. I also noticed, nothing like this was released for CSS, so I decided to. This map went through 5 or 6 versions, this being the last. Lots of starting over, and redoing. So, lets get on with this... ***Entry for kaos server mapping competition*** FEATURES: -20 levels (Most are never before seen on CSS) -js_build_puzzle style -Lobby -Bowling (see credits) -Magic 8 Ball -Slot Machine (see credits) -Juke Box -Secret getaway island that includes the last 4 things mentioned -Point System -Some detail here and there, not my main focus -No hdr (not really a feature, just thought you should know) -Fun (hopefully) LEVELS: Level 1: The Art of Rotation Level 2: Hot Rafting Level 3: Lost in the Clouds Level 4: Explosive Golf Level 5: Find The Nothing Level 6: Stuck In Traffic (Theres a bit of a story behind this one, see below) Level 7: Up Yours, Gravity Level 8: Light 'Em Up Level 9: Flashed Level 10: Man The Cannons (It's a pun) Level 11: Rolling Stones Level 12: Water-Hopper Level 13: Drug Test Level 14: The Path To Freedom...Or Certain Death Level 15: Dumb Luck Level 16: Smoking Kills (Glitchy, sometimes a few don't go under and the level fails to work) Level 17: Wishing Well Doesn't Work Against Death Level 18: Doin' Somethin' Stupid Level 19: It's Alright, I also said WTF (I ran out of titles OK?) Level 20: Because What's An Obstacle Map Without Lasers? LEVEL 6: Well, theres a story behind this one. I know this looks almost exactly like the one from the space js_build_puzzle map, but the fact is...its not. This level is the ONLY level that made it from the bob4 phaze, and I had this idea long before I played the D@Sole's map. However, mine was...broken (???) and I had a friend decompile the space one for me to check out the little car level. I DID NOT steal it, I made my own from scratch. I did follow his example on the things I had problems with, such as the path_tracks, but yet again, I DID NOT steal the level, had the idea long before I saw his map. However, if D@sole has a problem with it I can update the map with a new level 6, but I want to hear from him first. OVERVIEW: I'm not going to lie here. I'm one of those nerds who have nothing better to do than practice my obstacle skills. For me, this map is mediumish, I can do it, but with some problems. For the sake of the children (lol) I threw in some easy ones, ones that require teamwork, and ones that are easy but take a while to do. This map will have rage quitting, and more sadly, "ragertving." Level 1: The name gives it away Level 2: Navigate your floating platform on the magic flying river Level 3: Requires teamwork, throw nades into holes to move platforms Level 4: Get all barrels into the holes Level 5: Knife around the edges, and follow the white/grey particles Level 6: Dodge cars while moving through traffic Level 7: Low Gravity Jumping, EXTREMELY EASY Level 8: Use your flashlight to find the path Level 9: Navigate yourself through a room thats all white Level 10: Shoot teammates to towers, they press buttons there, then they must die. Level 11: Push a ball across the path Level 12: Hard to explain, as seen in tomgreen's obstacles and asdf, the water in mid air thing Level 13: Do an obstacle course while your drunk (actually pretty hard) Level 14: Try to not get shot by the aliens Level 15: Choose the right path, random each time. Level 16: Throw smokes over the wall onto the CT's heads (glitchy, as stated above) Level 17: Dig the tunnel while underwater Level 18: Jump on a moving plane Level 19: Jump on the spinning thing and avoid being pushed off Level 20: Hope you dont get hit on your way down the hallway. KNOWN BUGZ: -Level 16 SOMETIMES (1/10) glitches and is unplayable. -People who join after 30 seconds of the map starting, MAY not hear the sounds CREDITS: -Disconnected - Made the map -Espilon - Made the hut on the island -evjand - Made the slot machine on the island -PcmciaKai - Made the bowling alley on the island (I got lazy on the island, sue me :P) -All the other textures I found on cgtextures.com or on google. Some (like hardwood floor) werre also made by PcmciaKai. -karatekäfer - skybox texture -Also thanks to D@sole for inspiring me to make this map, you make awsome maps dude. CONDITIONS: By reading this (the three words you just read), and/or by downloading the map, you agree to not to release any modified versions of the map and not to release any parts of the map to the public without getting my permission. PM me for the vmf. as I hope a lot of people use this map as an example for their next obstacle map. HAVE FUN!!!! By the way: For every person that downloads this, plays it, and does not post a response here, a puppy AND a kitty die. I'm cold like that... No, really, post responses, they help me help you by helping me understand what makes this map better. Also, if anyone can tell me who made the lava texture, I'll give them a dollar, I remember downloading it from here, but the site's search is screwy for me at the moment. PM me for the vmf. If you put on your server let me know, I'll come check it out. EDIT: I uploaded some decent screenshots also, but fpsbanana screwed it over on that one, so view them in the seperate page, you'll see some more then given. KTHXBAI

Course map originally named mg_gore_course_b1, created by ScHoOuFi and La Boule (original). I just took the map and fixed all of the leaks and optimized it a bit.

The sole purpose of this 'fix' was to improve performance on low-end PCs. So, for those still using toasters to play CS:S (including myself), this is for you. (~30 FPS on high settings looking down the hallway from spawn in original; 90-100 FPS in optimized version)

Changes:
- Optimization and leak fixes; previously, the entire map was rendered at once. Areaportals have been placed at every door
- Ice skate ramp is now a simple brush rather than a displacement, should no longer stop you
- Spawn timer changed from 10s to 30s; screen shake drastically reduced to avoid annoyance
- Secret trails adjusted a bit
- Added more player spawns.
- The floating sofa in level 3 has a static orientation.
- maybe some more I forgot about

I do not take any credit for creating this map; all credit belongs to the other authors listed under "Original Authors" above.
